# T1071.001 — Application Layer Protocol: DNS

**Detection #3 — DNS Beaconing / Tunneling via Sysmon Event 22**

---

## Summary

This case study documents the detection of DNS-based command-and-control (C2) beaconing behavior using Sysmon Event ID 22 (DNS query) ingested into Splunk. The detection identifies a process issuing a high volume of DNS queries to many unique subdomains under a single parent domain — a fingerprint shared by DNS tunneling tools (dnscat2, Iodine), C2 frameworks with DNS beacon channels (Cobalt Strike, Sliver, Mythic), and several malware families that exfiltrate data through DNS labels.

