## Simulation

I built a standalone PowerShell script to reproduce the beacon pattern: [`scripts/simulation/Invoke-DnsBeaconSimulation.ps1`](../../scripts/simulation/Invoke-DnsBeaconSimulation.ps1)

The script:

- Flushes the local DNS cache (so every query produces network activity and a corresponding Sysmon event)
- Issues N DNS queries to unique subdomains under a configurable parent domain
- Optionally adds randomized jitter between queries to mimic real C2 evasion behavior
- Logs each query with timestamp for correlation against Sysmon/Splunk telemetry

Default invocation:

```powershell
.\Invoke-DnsBeaconSimulation.ps1
# 20 queries to evil-lab-domain.xyz, ~3s intervals, ~60s total runtime
```

Realistic-jitter run:

```powershell
.\Invoke-DnsBeaconSimulation.ps1 -Count 30 -IntervalSeconds 10 -Jitter
```

**Safety:** The script issues only DNS queries to a non-routable lab domain. No payloads, no real C2 infrastructure contacted, no malicious code executes. The activity is purely network telemetry generation.

